"{\"uid\": \"cryptopolitan.com-france-leads-with-ai-for-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"France recently conducted a successful trial run of Artificial Intelligence-driven video surveillance technology during a Depeche Mode concert.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8310639395561235, \"rank\": 0.19490295768269833, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The exercise served as a litmus test for the forthcoming Olympic Games, showcasing the efficacy of the AI-powered surveillance system.\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 279, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The trial's success underscores the nation's commitment to leveraging advanced technology to bolster security measures during large-scale events.\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French legislation enacted in 2023 paved the way for the utilization of AI video surveillance during the trial period encompassing the Paris 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 428, \"to\": 583, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 428, \"end\": 434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9386936274491418, \"rank\": 0.04609743400463835, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 500, \"end\": 502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.799756870770666e-26, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This innovative approach employs algorithmic video surveillance, utilizing computer software to analyze real-time images captured by surveillance cameras.\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 739, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Four prominent companies - Videtics, Orange Business, ChapsVision, and Wintics - have spearheaded the development of AI software, employing sophisticated algorithms to detect potential threats and abnormal behavior in public spaces.\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 777, \"end\": 783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7529148904845448e-14, \"text\": \"Orange\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\"}, {\"begin\": 857, \"end\": 859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.799756870770666e-26, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The AI algorithms are meticulously trained to identify predefined \\\"events\\\" and aberrant activities, promptly triggering alerts for human intervention.\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 978, \"end\": 980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.799756870770666e-26, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These events encompass a spectrum of potential security concerns, including crowd surges, abandoned objects, and the presence or use of weapons, among others.\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Furthermore, specific thresholds can be manually configured to cater to individual event types, locations, or threats, enhancing the system's adaptability and efficacy.\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1454, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"National and local law enforcement agencies, firefighters, and public transport security personnel will be equipped with access to AI-powered surveillance systems.\", \"from\": 1456, \"to\": 1619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Notably, Wintics' software, which underwent successful testing at the Depeche Mode concert, will be deployed across the Paris region and integrated into public transport networks.\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1741, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999713822949, \"rank\": 2.8617536436370843e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Police Chief Laurent Nunez lauded the trial's outcome, expressing confidence in the system's readiness for widespread implementation.\", \"from\": 1802, \"to\": 1941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1802, \"end\": 1807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999713822949, \"rank\": 2.8617536436370843e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the technological advancements, French authorities have unequivocally stated that facial recognition will not be employed, citing concerns regarding privacy and civil liberties.\", \"from\": 1943, \"to\": 2128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1983, \"end\": 1989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9386936274491418, \"rank\": 0.04609743400463835, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The legislation firmly prohibits facial recognition in most scenarios, emphasizing the government's commitment to safeguarding individual rights.\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, rights campaigners remain vigilant, wary of potential mission creep and the gradual expansion of surveillance capabilities.\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2409, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To address privacy and civil liberties concerns, France's Interior Ministry has established an evaluation committee tasked with monitoring the AI surveillance system's compliance with legal and ethical standards.\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2460, \"end\": 2466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8310639395561235, \"rank\": 0.19490295768269833, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2469, \"end\": 2486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Ministry_of_the_Interior_and_Community\", \"score\": 0.798254667805849, \"rank\": 0.2527330441407651, \"text\": \"Interior Ministry\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Ministry_of_the_Interior_and_Community\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Ministry_of_the_Interior_and_Community\"}, {\"begin\": 2554, \"end\": 2556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.799756870770666e-26, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Led by a senior official from France's top administrative court, the committee includes representatives from the country's privacy watchdog, CNIL, as well as lawmakers and municipal authorities.\", \"from\": 2625, \"to\": 2819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2655, \"end\": 2661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8310639395561235, \"rank\": 0.19490295768269833, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This multifaceted oversight mechanism aims to strike a delicate balance between security imperatives and individual rights.\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 2944, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France's proactive adoption of AI-powered surveillance represents a pivotal step towards ensuring the safety and security of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 3100, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2946, \"end\": 2952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8310639395561235, \"rank\": 0.19490295768269833, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While leveraging cutting-edge technology, the nation remains steadfast in upholding privacy rights and civil liberties, underscored by its stringent regulations and comprehensive oversight framework.\", \"from\": 3102, \"to\": 3301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the world looks ahead to the spectacle of the Olympics, France stands at the forefront of innovative security measures, setting a precedent for future mega-events.\", \"from\": 3303, \"to\": 3469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3362, \"end\": 3368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8310639395561235, \"rank\": 0.19490295768269833, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The smartest crypto minds already read our newsletter.\", \"from\": 3471, \"to\": 3525, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Want in?Join them.\", \"from\": 3526, \"to\": 3544, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Disclaimer.The information provided is not trading advice.Cryptopolitan.comholds no liability for any investments made based on the information provided on this page.\", \"from\": 3546, \"to\": 3712, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We strongly recommend independent research and/or consultation with a qualified professional before making any investment decisions  Stay informed with Cryptopolitan's newsletters - delivered straight to your inbox.\", \"from\": 3713, \"to\": 3928, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your gateway to web3.\", \"from\": 3930, \"to\": 3951, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright 2025 Cryptopolitan  Subscribe to Cryptopolitan Daily and get timely, sharp, and relevant crypto insights straight to your inbox.\", \"from\": 3953, \"to\": 4091, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join now andnever miss a move.\", \"from\": 4093, \"to\": 4123, \"entities\": []}]}"